          },
          "displayName": "Wangda Tan",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
        },
        "body": "Thanks [~qinchen@microsoft.com]/Myeongjae for filing the JIRA and uploading design docs. \r\n\r\nAs discussed offline, even though I think the ideal case is to let YARN understand GPU hierarchy and assign GPUs with best interconnect. I'm still looking to bring this effort forward since this enables some use cases of GPU and I can see the common functionalities of local resource affinity can be reused by other features as well (for example network/SSDs/CPU, etc.).\r\n\r\nRegarding to the design / prototype:\r\n\r\nThe proposed approach added one more field to the resource class. I'm not sure what's the best solution of this. Probably we can add a new type to {{org.apache.hadoop.yarn.api.protocolrecords.ResourceTypes}} (Such as vector/bitmap, etc.), and an inherited ResourceInformation class to return the vector/bitmap. Bitmap/vector type will be excluded from scheduling / DRF calculation, etc. \r\n\r\n+ folks who might be interested in this effort:\r\n\r\n[~subru]/[~sunilg]/[~vvasudev]/[~templedf]/[~asuresh]/[~jlowe]. ",
        "updateAuthor": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=leftnoteasy",
          "name": "leftnoteasy",
          "key": "leftnoteasy",
